         <cite class="fn">andy_o</cite>      </div>
      

      <div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://drop-kicker.com/2014/03/smarty-ring-runs-second-fundraiser-allows-backers-to-pay-more-for-confusing-upgrade/#comment-5054">March 26, 2014 at 2:02 pm</a>     
           </div>
      <div class="clear"></div>
     
     </div>
     

	<div class="commentbody">
      <p>I had in mind something like that, actually. Not for you to review those kooky products I mentioned above, but if you had found any correlation between scams and &#8220;flexible funding&#8221; campaigns. To me it seems that the most unbelievable ones are always flexible funding, but that could just be confirmation bias.</p>

